1. Normal document flow:
a. block elements- elements that stretch the entire web page or display on your browser
Always strat on a new line
b. in-line elements- take as much space as they need: 
e.g links, span, and also images

2. Display property- shows how an element should display
a. block = 
b. inline = takes as much space sa they require
c. inline-block = instructing the elements to behave like inline but you cannot change the length or width
d. none = simply hiding the elements completely. Not visible on the browser
e. flex = turns the container into a flexible layout
f. read = turns the container into a read layout: rowsa and columns in a table
g. float----it is outdated = shift/push elements to one side- right/left